                                                    <h2>How it works <a href="" id="How-it-works"
                                                            class="opacity-0 hover-1">#</a></h2>
                                                    <p>Here's what you need to know before getting started with the
                                                        navbar:</p>
                                                    <ul class=" un_order_list ">
                                                        <li>
                                                        Navbars need to be wrapped.navbar with the classes <code>.navbar-expand{sm|-md|-lg|-xl|-xxl}</code> for responsive collapsing.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        Navbars and the items they contain are by default fluid. The container can be modified to limit their horizontal width in many ways.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        To manage spacing and alignment within navbars, use our utility classes for spacing and flex.

                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        By default, navbars are responsive, but you can simply change that. Dependent on our Collapse JavaScript plugin for responsive behavior.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        Make sure the site is accessible by using a nav element or, if using a more generic element like a div, by adding a role="navigation" to each navbar to expressly indicate it as a landmark area for people using assistive technologies.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        Use <code>aria-current="page"</code> to indicate the current page or <code>aria-current="true"</code> to indicate the current item in a set.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        <code>.navbar-light</code> has been deprecated and .navbar can now be themed with CSS variables that are scoped to the.navbar base class. Instead of adding more styles, navbar-dark has been rewritten to override CSS variables.E402
                                                        </li>
                                                    </ul>

                                                    <div class="bd-callout bd-callout-info blockquote mt-20">The
                                                        animation effect of this component is dependent on the
                                                        <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> media query. See the <a
                                                            href="#">reduced motion section of our accessibility
                                                            documentation</a>.
                                                    </div>
                                                    <h1 class="mt-20">Supported content <a href=""
                                                            id="Supported-content" class="opacity-0 hover-1">#</a></h1>
                                                    <p>For use with our collapse plugin and other navigation toggling behaviors, see <code>.navbar-toggler</code>.</p>
                                                    <ul class="un_order_list mt-20">
                                                        <li>
                                                        Utilities for flex and spacing for all form actions and controls.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        For adding vertically centered text strings, use .navbar-text.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                        For grouping and hiding navbar contents by a parent breakpoint, use .collapse.navbar-collapse.
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>Include an optional.To establish a maximum height and scroll expanding navbar content, use navbar-scroll.</li>
                                                        
